Product Information

  • Here is a top-of-the-range DJI Mavic Pro 4k Camera Drone Quadcopter which will be a boon both for the serious film maker as well as the enthusiastic amateur. As well as standard spec, of the other models in the real market; this model also features HD video recording with many variants and in a choice of dpi resolutions.   • by simo_hastiJul 08, 2018

    Best fun I ever had with my clothes on.

    I got this as a ‘toe in the water’ experiment with aerial photography and video. It’s more than done it’s job in this respect and has led to my working towards a PfCO so that I can legitimately include aerial work in my media business. Not the absolute best image quality, but surprisingly good considering the sensor size and lens involved. With realistic expectations, a little common sense regarding light levels and a decent set of polarising ND filters, both stills and video are good enough for low level commercial work (which is exactly what I do). Depending upon how demand grows for aerial work within my business, I may well upgrade to something more capable in the future, but in the meantime this little Mavic will do nicely. All that serious workman stuff aside, this thing is also a trRead full review

    Perfectly compact drone

    As a newcomer I have just made my first flight! I do need more practice but my first impressions are that it is well designed and built. As far as flying goes, a doddle, even for me although I do have a pilots licence for somewhat bigger machines. I am a photographer and mainly interested in stills. This is does excellently. What more is there to be said? I would certainly recommend to any enthusiast. John. Llandudno.
